    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-01T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-01T08:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-01T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 1, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 1—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. A letter from the office of General Queipo de Llano<note n="36"
                        xml:id="d122fn36">Nationalist general in command of Seville area.</note> has
                    been received this morning which in translation reads as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Minister of Foreign Affairs of the National Government in Burgos has
                            requested me to inform you that in order to discuss various questions an
                            interview with the chiefs of that Ministry would be convenient. <pb
                                facs="0179" n="171" xml:id="pg_171"/> He desires that the interview
                            take place in Burgos and that he be informed of the date of your arrival
                            in that capital.</p>
                        <p>In communicating the foregoing it is requested that you indicate to me
                            for communication to the mentioned authority when you shall make the
                            trip.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Will the Department inform me what answer should be made to this
                    communication?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
